From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi: Thread DualSense mono AudioEndpoint skip flag.

Spider-Man Remastered needs the DualSense mono speaker MMDevice so FAudio can
open it for controller speaker effects. However, exposing that same 1-channel
controller speaker as a normal fake SWD\MMDEVAPI AudioEndpoint also makes the
game's managed audio endpoint enumeration see an extra render endpoint and
crash with an InvalidCastException at startup.

Add the registration flag used by the follow-up patches to skip only the fake
PnP AudioEndpoint registration for the DualSense mono speaker.
---
 dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
index dc36ab2ab89..cb6bf9e8fb0 100644
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -751,6 +751,6 @@ static void remove_dualsense_media_devices(void)
 }
 
 static void MMDevice_Register(const WCHAR *instguid, const WCHAR *friendly_name, const WCHAR *device_iname, const WCHAR *device_path,
-        const GUID *container_id, EDataFlow flow)
+        const GUID *container_id, BOOL skip_audioendpoint, EDataFlow flow)
 {
     static const WCHAR ControlClass[] = L"System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Class";
     static const WCHAR AudioEndpoint_Class[] = L"AudioEndpoint";
-- 
